'1:31': [
{sup:"a", word:"holding", vrefs:"Mark 5:41; 9:27; Acts 3:7"},
{sup:1, word:"left", lines:["Sickness issues from sin and is a sign of man&rsquo;s abnormal condition before God because of sin. The fourth thing the Slave-Savior did to rescue the sinners, as another part of His gospel service, was to heal their sick condition physically and spiritually and restore them to normality ({Mrk1:34|v. 34}; {Mrk3:10|3:10}; {Mrk6:5|6:5}, {Mrk6:13|13}, {Mrk6:56|56}) that they might serve Him. Nine cases are recorded in this Gospel to illustrate such healing (vv. {Mrk1:30|30}-{Mrk1:31|31}, {Mrk1:40|40}-{Mrk1:45|45}; {Mrk2:3|2:3}-{Mrk2:12|12}; {Mrk3:1|3:1}-{Mrk3:5|5}; {Mrk5:22|5:22}-{Mrk5:43|43}; {Mrk7:32|7:32}-{Mrk7:37|37}; {Mrk8:22|8:22}-{Mrk8:26|26}; {Mrk10:46|10:46}-{Mrk10:52|52})."]},
{sup:2, word:"served", lines:["First she was healed, then she served."]},
],
